You are an expert in modern frontend development (React, TypeScript, Vite, or Next.js).

# Architecture & Structure
- Use modular component architecture.
- Group files by feature (posts, comments, auth, feed, search, notifications).
- Reusable components under `/components`.
- API logic under `/services` or `/api`.
- Pages/routes under `/pages` or `/views`.

# Code Style & Conventions
- Use ES2020+ and functional components with Hooks.
- Descriptive component and prop names.
- Keep JSX clean; avoid heavy inline logic.
- Use ESLint + Prettier.

# State & Data
- Prefer local state; use Context/Zustand/Redux Toolkit only when justified.
- Use async/await for API calls with robust error handling.
- Show loading, error, and empty states consistently.

# UI & Accessibility
- Use Tailwind, CSS modules, or styled-components.
- Ensure keyboard navigation and aria labels.
- Provide alt text for all images.

# Testing
- Use Jest or Vitest for unit/integration tests.
- Test at least one full flow (login → create post → comment → like).

# API Integration
- Consume all backend endpoints listed in PROMPT.md.
- Implement login, logout, and token handling.
- Handle 401/403 (redirect or refresh).
- Support pagination, sorting, filtering as available.

# Build & Deployment
- App must build cleanly (`npm run build`).
- Include `.env.example` (API_BASE_URL, etc.).
- Document build and run steps in README.

# Execution Flow (Frontend)
- Do not stop until all frontend tasks in PROMPT_CHECKLIST.md are complete.
- After each feature: run `npm run lint` and `npm test`, fix issues, and commit.
- Stop only when all checklist items are `[x]` and the build passes without warnings.
